                "name": "Teams",
                "url": "/topics/teams"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277429",
        "quote": "This was nostalgia in the literal Greek sense: the pain of not being able to return to one's home and family.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277429"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Pain",
                "url": "/topics/pain"
            },
            {
                "name": "Nostalgia",
                "url": "/topics/nostalgia"
            },
            {
                "name": "Greek",
                "url": "/topics/greek"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277432",
        "quote": "We are fans because the game also appeals to our local pride, our pleasure in thinking of ourselves as, yes, Americans but nonetheless different from residents of other towns, other states, other regions.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277432"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Game",
                "url": "/topics/game"
            },
            {
                "name": "Other",
                "url": "/topics/other"
            },
            {
                "name": "Regions",
                "url": "/topics/regions"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277435",
        "quote": "We know these men are professionals whose services are up for bid and whose bags are packed, and yet we call them our own and take personal, even civic pride in their accomplishments.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277435"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Own",
                "url": "/topics/own"
            },
            {
                "name": "Bags",
                "url": "/topics/bags"
            },
            {
                "name": "Professionals",
                "url": "/topics/professionals"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277437",
        "quote": "Why we play as children is not because it is our work or because it is how we learn, though both statements are true; we play because we are wired for joy, it is imperative as human beings.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277437"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Play",
                "url": "/topics/play"
            },
            {
                "name": "Wired",
                "url": "/topics/wired"
            },
            {
                "name": "Though",
                "url": "/topics/though"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277439",
        "quote": "Yes, we've seen it all before. And yes, those who do not study history are condemned to repeat it. But no, the sky is not falling - baseball is such a great game that neither the owners nor the players can kill it. After some necessary carnage, market forces will prevail.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277439"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Game",
                "url": "/topics/game"
            },
            {
                "name": "Study",
                "url": "/topics/study"
            },
            {
                "name": "Some",
                "url": "/topics/some"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277363",
        "quote": "Baseball presents a living heritage, a game poised between the powerful undertow of seasons past and the hope of next day, next week, next year.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277363"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Game",
                "url": "/topics/game"
            },
            {
                "name": "Seasons",
                "url": "/topics/seasons"
            },
            {
                "name": "Next",
                "url": "/topics/next"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277378",
        "quote": "For many in baseball September is a month of stark contrast with April, when everyone had dared to hope. If baseball is a lot like life, as pundits declare, it is because life is more about losing than winning.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277378"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Winning",
                "url": "/topics/winning"
            },
            {
                "name": "Everyone",
                "url": "/topics/everyone"
            },
            {
                "name": "Declare",
                "url": "/topics/declare"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277401",
        "quote": "My egotistical concern was less that I would fail to relate to my classmates than that they would know nothing of my uniquely tortured life's course and, thus, me.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277401"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Nothing",
                "url": "/topics/nothing"
            },
            {
                "name": "Tortured",
                "url": "/topics/tortured"
            },
            {
                "name": "Thus",
                "url": "/topics/thus"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277376",
        "quote": "Finally, for all of us but a lucky few, the dream of playing big-time baseball is relinquished so we can get on with grown-up things.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277376"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Lucky",
                "url": "/topics/lucky"
            },
            {
                "name": "Finally",
                "url": "/topics/finally"
            },
            {
                "name": "Grown-Up",
                "url": "/topics/grown-up"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277399",
        "quote": "More fundamentally, it is a dream that does not die with the onset of manhood: the dream is to play endlessly, past the time when you are called home for dinner, past the time of doing chores, past the time when your body betrays you past time itself.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277399"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Play",
                "url": "/topics/play"
            },
            {
                "name": "Die",
                "url": "/topics/die"
            },
            {
                "name": "Endlessly",
                "url": "/topics/endlessly"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277357",
        "quote": "As the game enters its glorious final weeks, the chill of fall signals the reality of defeat for all but one team. The fields of play will turn brown and harden, the snow will fall, but in the heart of the fan sprouts a sprig of green.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277357"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Game",
                "url": "/topics/game"
            },
            {
                "name": "Play",
                "url": "/topics/play"
            },
            {
                "name": "Weeks",
                "url": "/topics/weeks"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277413",
        "quote": "The caliber of play suffered and attendance declined year by year. Interest in college football was exploding, and there was this new game called basketball.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277413"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "College",
                "url": "/topics/college"
            },
            {
                "name": "Play",
                "url": "/topics/play"
            },
            {
                "name": "New",
                "url": "/topics/new"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277405",
        "quote": "Planning to play: that's what saving for retirement is today - and it is antithetical to the nature of play, fully within the definition of work, and blissfully ignorant of the reality of death.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277405"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Nature",
                "url": "/topics/nature"
            },
            {
                "name": "Death",
                "url": "/topics/death"
            },
            {
                "name": "Play",
                "url": "/topics/play"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277366",
        "quote": "Better than anything else in our culture, it enables fathers and sons to speak on a level playing field while building up from within a personal history of shared experience - a group history - that may be tapped into at will in years to come.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277366"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Shared",
                "url": "/topics/shared"
            },
            {
                "name": "Fathers",
                "url": "/topics/fathers"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277392",
        "quote": "In response to the challenge of strangers, sport arose as a sublimated representation of a community's armed might as well as its pride of place and clan.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277392"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Community",
                "url": "/topics/community"
            },
            {
                "name": "Strangers",
                "url": "/topics/strangers"
            },
            {
                "name": "Might",
                "url": "/topics/might"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_171810",
        "quote": "Whatever else I do before finally I go to my grave, I hope it will not be looking after young people.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_171810"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Grave",
                "url": "/topics/grave"
            },
            {
                "name": "Will",
                "url": "/topics/will"
            },
            {
                "name": "Before",
                "url": "/topics/before"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277355",
        "quote": "And then came the nineties, when management, suddenly frightened that they had ceded control to the players, sought to restore baseball's profitability by 'running the game like a business.'",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277355"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Game",
                "url": "/topics/game"
            },
            {
                "name": "Profitability",
                "url": "/topics/profitability"
            },
            {
                "name": "Restore",
                "url": "/topics/restore"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277360",
        "quote": "Award trophies, as opposed to letting the players define and claim their own. Ultimately, pay them to play so that their activity not only resembles work but is work.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277360"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Play",
                "url": "/topics/play"
            },
            {
                "name": "Activity",
                "url": "/topics/activity"
            },
            {
                "name": "Opposed",
                "url": "/topics/opposed"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277367",
        "quote": "But baseball bounced back in the next decade to reclaim its place as the national pastime: new heroes, spirited competition, and booming prosperity gave birth to dreams of expansion, both within the major leagues and around the world.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277367"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Back",
                "url": "/topics/back"
            },
            {
                "name": "Next",
                "url": "/topics/next"
            },
            {
                "name": "Decade",
                "url": "/topics/decade"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277368",
        "quote": "But the citizens of Cincinnati loved their Reds because they won, no matter what their addresses had been the year before. They rooted for the Old-English 'C' on the players' shirts.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277368"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Year",
                "url": "/topics/year"
            },
            {
                "name": "Before",
                "url": "/topics/before"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277369",
        "quote": "But the dream is never forgotten, only put aside and never out of reach: Where once the dream connected boys with the world of men, now it reconnects men with the spirit of boys.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277369"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Spirit",
                "url": "/topics/spirit"
            },
            {
                "name": "Reach",
                "url": "/topics/reach"
            },
            {
                "name": "Put",
                "url": "/topics/put"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277370",
        "quote": "Distant replay morphs into instant replay, and future replay cannot be far off.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277370"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Future",
                "url": "/topics/future"
            },
            {
                "name": "Distant",
                "url": "/topics/distant"
            },
            {
                "name": "Far",
                "url": "/topics/far"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277371",
        "quote": "Do we settle on a regional team because we can go to its ballpark and see its games on television? Or do we choose a team as our favorite because it has an especially appealing player, a Barry Bonds or an Ichiro?",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277371"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Television",
                "url": "/topics/television"
            },
            {
                "name": "Settle",
                "url": "/topics/settle"
            },
            {
                "name": "Regional",
                "url": "/topics/regional"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277372",
        "quote": "Donning a glove for a backyard toss, or watching a ball game, or just reflecting upon our baseball days, we are players again, forever young.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277372"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Game",
                "url": "/topics/game"
            },
            {
                "name": "Young",
                "url": "/topics/young"
            },
            {
                "name": "Players",
                "url": "/topics/players"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277379",
        "quote": "For many of us, sport has provided the continuity in our lives, the alternative family to the one we left behind. It gives us something to talk about, to preen about, to care about.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277379"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Behind",
                "url": "/topics/behind"
            },
            {
                "name": "Lives",
                "url": "/topics/lives"
            },
            {
                "name": "Provided",
                "url": "/topics/provided"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277387",
        "quote": "I think that much of this was running in background as I contemplated whether or not to attend the PS 99 reunion, although I certainly anticipated that I would not; it smelled like death, not youth.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277387"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Think",
                "url": "/topics/think"
            },
            {
                "name": "I Think",
                "url": "/topics/i_think"
            },
            {
                "name": "Contemplated",
                "url": "/topics/contemplated"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277388",
        "quote": "If I haven't made myself clear, this worrisome chain of events describes the game of the nineteenth century.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277388"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Game",
                "url": "/topics/game"
            },
            {
                "name": "Chain",
                "url": "/topics/chain"
            },
            {
                "name": "Made",
                "url": "/topics/made"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277391",
        "quote": "In over 160 years of recorded baseball history, no team had ever won a championship this way.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277391"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Over",
                "url": "/topics/over"
            },
            {
                "name": "Had",
                "url": "/topics/had"
            },
            {
                "name": "Baseball History",
                "url": "/topics/baseball_history"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277402",
        "quote": "One of the first lessons he or she learns is that in baseball anything, absolutely anything, can happen. Just two days ago as I write this, something happened that had never happened in baseball before.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277402"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Happen",
                "url": "/topics/happen"
            },
            {
                "name": "Before",
                "url": "/topics/before"
            },
            {
                "name": "I Write",
                "url": "/topics/i_write"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277406",
        "quote": "Pursuing employment or climatic relief, we live in voluntary exile from our extended families and our longer past, but in an involuntary exile from ourselves and our own past.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277406"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Past",
                "url": "/topics/past"
            },
            {
                "name": "Own",
                "url": "/topics/own"
            },
            {
                "name": "Pursuing",
                "url": "/topics/pursuing"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277416",
        "quote": "The heroes of our youth grow old - 'the boys of summer in their ruin', in Dylan Thomas's verse - yet we seem the same.",
        "author": {
            "name": "John Thorn",
            "url": "/quotes/john_thorn_277416"
        },
